<TITLE> Struggling freedom fighters' allowance up </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 10 (bdnews24.com)  Finance minister AMA Muhith has proposed a TK 500 monthly rise in the individual allowance for financially insolvent freedom fighters. The proposed allowance stands at Tk 2,000 per month. Another 25,000 beneficiaries will also be added under this scheme making the total 150,000 individuals, the minister said. The tota proposedl allocation is set to rise to 61.11 crore for the FY 2010-11. In his budget speech Muhith said efforts to identify genuine freedom fighters has already started, in line with plans to bring all living freedom fighters into the fold of a regular allowance system. After the scrutiny is over a policy will be formulated to grant a similar allowance to all freedom fighters. An allocation of Tk 17.18 crore has been proposed to revive the Bangladesh Freedom Fighters Welfare Trust from its precarious state of insolvency. 
